      "writtenOn": "2020-11-02T20:48:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "`terminated \u003c- true` is to ensure that the goroutine is not in process of invoking printSummary(). close(channel) doesn\u0027t block the caller.\n\nI moved L247 to L256, as you suggested, but I still like to keep it a boolean channel to ensure that the final summary gets printed out before runTestCmd() returns to the caller. If this defer() simply closes the channel, it\u0027s possible that the sink process terminates before the goroutine prints the summary.",
